Reading

What are the benefits of a forward proxy?
-Being able to avoid institutional or state restrictions while perusing the web.
-The ability to block certain groups from accessing content.
-The ability to use the IP of the Proxy in order to conceal their own IP.

Explain the differences between a forward and a reverse proxy?
A forward proxy is in service in front of the client ensuring an origin server doesn't directly interact 
with a client.  A reverse proxy is in service in front of the origin server ensuring a client doesn't directly interact 
with the server.  

Explain to your manager why your organization might benefit from implementing a reverse proxy?
A reverse proxy is another layer of encryption and security as well a tool to balance traffic (load balancing). 
Additionally, the ability to cache website data helps to increase speed and service performance. 

